HEADWORD: Dinaphthyl
<hw>Di*naph"thyl</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>di-</ets> + <ets>naphthyl</ets>ene.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>A colorless, crystalline hydrocarbon, <chform>C20H14</chform>,
obtained from naphthylene, and consisting of a doubled naphthylene
radical.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

